x4freetext: Si, S, Ca, Cu, La, Pb, 209Bi, 238U on figs.
Four NE213 liquid scintillation detectors and
four monitors were located together with the neutron-
production target and a spin-flip magnet in a close
doubly-shielded geometry. The contribution of gamma-
rays was kept below 1% by means of n-gamma
discrimination. The resolution of the neutron
Data were corrected for flux attenuation, multiple
scattering and depolarization in the samples.
The authors do not say "elastic", but compiler
authors try exclude the scattered neutrons slower
believes the than those from elastic scattering.
However, the experiment could not exclude excitation
to low-lying levels due to poor energy resolution of
0.8 MeV, and therefore these datasets are partial
scatteing datasets when there are excitation levels
The differential cross sections and analyzing
powers are given with the statistical errors only.
